00:06:06.750 --> 00:06:07.720
MICHAEL VOLTAGGIO: We're with you.

00:06:07.720 --> 00:06:09.010
MICHAEL BRENNER: And
this is very important.

00:06:09.010 --> 00:06:10.843
And I want to basically
tell you about this.

00:06:10.843 --> 00:06:16.117
So the point is that when the volume
fraction is less than 64% or so, then

00:06:16.117 --> 00:06:16.700
it's a liquid.

00:06:16.700 --> 00:06:17.550
It flows.

00:06:17.550 --> 00:06:20.197
That's why when I did this--

00:06:20.197 --> 00:06:21.690
[RATTLING]

00:06:21.690 --> 00:06:22.330
--it flowed.

00:06:22.330 --> 00:06:25.580
When it's 64% or bigger, than
it has an elastic modulus.

00:06:25.580 --> 00:06:26.980
It's a solid.

00:06:26.980 --> 00:06:29.990
So you can plot the elasticity
as a function of volume fraction.

00:06:29.990 --> 00:06:31.865
And there's a critical
volume fraction, which

00:06:31.865 --> 00:06:36.330
is 64%, where basically
the thing becomes a solid.

00:06:36.330 --> 00:06:40.690
And as you continue to compress it above
that, it becomes more and more stiff.

00:06:40.690 --> 00:06:43.370
