single day, every time we cook,

00:46:10.480 --> 00:46:12.080
or at least a lot of times.

00:46:12.080 --> 00:46:17.380
So a pasta dish, just thinking
spaghetti and a marinara sauce.

00:46:17.380 --> 00:46:21.315
But if you're adding olive oil, and
butter, and some pasta water to it

00:46:21.315 --> 00:46:24.190
because you're making it correctly,
we want some of that starch water

00:46:24.190 --> 00:46:25.040
into there.

00:46:25.040 --> 00:46:27.500
That starch is going to
help create that emulsion

00:46:27.500 --> 00:46:31.122
and make that suspended sauce that's
going to coat the pasta all over

00:46:31.122 --> 00:46:32.330
and make it really delicious.

00:46:32.330 --> 00:46:35.789
That way every time you're grabbing
a noodle-- I mean I know some of us

00:46:35.789 --> 00:46:37.830
take the jar of spaghetti
and you boil the pasta.

00:46:37.830 --> 00:46:39.460
MICHAEL VOLTAGGIO: Did
you say grabbing a noodle?

00:46:39.460 --> 00:46:41.376
BRYAN VOLTAGGIO: Well,
yeah, you eat a noodle.

00:46:41.376 --> 00:46:43.134
